  "footnotes": [
    "Bosnian Banate: Semi-autonomous unit under nominal Hungarian suzerainty; the Bosnian Church (neither Catholic nor Orthodox) flourished here in the 13th–15th centuries.",
    "Duchy of Saint Sava: Named for the Serbian patron saint; Herceg Stefan Vukčić Kosača gave Herzegovina its name ('herceg' = duke).",
    "Bosnia-Herzegovina Condominium: The only Austro-Hungarian territory jointly administered by both halves of the empire rather than assigned to either; the 1908 annexation was a major trigger of the 1914 crisis.",
    "NDH (Independent State of Croatia): The Axis puppet state committed mass atrocities against Serbs, Jews, and Roma; Jasenovac concentration camp was on Bosnian territory.",
    "Dayton Agreement (1995): Divided BiH into two entities — Federation of BiH (~51%) and Republika Srpska (~49%) — with Brčko District as a self-governing district."
  ]
